## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to combine TLS edge proxying with per-tenant feature gates loaded from a daemon-managed config source. It also checks bootstrap discipline in a two-DC setup.

## Key Concepts
- Docker Configs for runtime config
- TLS termination at Nginx edge proxy
- Per-tenant feature gates in a small API
- Simple bootstrap for tenants and flags

## Code Example
```javascript
const fs = require('fs');
const yaml = require('js-yaml');
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
let flags = {};
function loadFlags() {
  const txt = fs.readFileSync('/etc/feature-flags.yaml','utf8');
  flags = yaml.load(txt) || {};
}
loadFlags();
app.get('/health-quiz', (req, res) => {
  const tenant = req.headers['x-tenant-id'];
  if (tenant && flags[tenant] && flags[tenant].enabled) res.sendStatus(200);
  else res.sendStatus(403);
});
app.listen(3000);
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you test this gating with CI and two data centers?
- What are failure modes if the config-loader container is unavailable?

## Why This Is Asked
This tests automation, Vault + SPIFFE integration, and zero-downtime trust reconfiguration across DCs.

## Key Concepts
- Vault CA bundles and SPIFFE trust anchors
- SPIFFE SVID rotation and edge-proxy hot-reload
- Idempotence, rollback, and verification across DCs

## Code Example
```javascript
// bootstrap trust distribution (pseudocode)
async function bootstrapCrossDC(dc) {
  await fetchTrustAnchors(dc);
  await rotateSVIDs(dc);
  await hotReloadProxies(dc);
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you test drift between trust material and service SVIDs?
- How do you handle partial failures during bootstrap (e.g., one DC unreachable)?

## Why This Is Asked

Tests depth of cross-DC security, dynamic policy loading, and automated risk controls in a real-world Docker DC architecture.

## Key Concepts

- SPIFFE/SVIDs with Vault
- WASM-based per-tenant policy engine
- Edge verifier sidecar for SVID validation
- Canary deployments and automatic rollback
- Cross-DC routing and observability

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo: load tenant policy from broker and validate SVID before calling app
async function handleRequest(req){
  const svid = await verifySVID(req.headers['spiffe']);
  const(policy) = await loadPolicyFromBroker(req.tenant);
  if(!policy.allows(req)) throw new Error('Access denied');
  return proxyToApp(req);
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you debug a scenario where Vault rotation invalidates existing SVIDs mid-rollout?
- What metrics and traces would you collect to enforce the 25% canary SLA thresholds across DCs?
